pos_sentences: The infrastructure has recently been renovated. The campus overall is quite good. Engineering, architecture and pharmacy are also located in the same campus. The entire campus is surrounded by lush trees, adding to it's beauty.
The patient inflow at hitkarini is far better than any other dental college in the region, giving opportunity of good patient exposure.
reviews.title: HDCH at a glance
reviews.name: Vartika

content.title: Admission
content.content: Any student who has appeared in the NEET-UG exam and has cleared the minimum eligibility score can apply for counseling through MPonline portal. The college will be allotted based on the scores. The student must choose hitkarini as their first choice of college.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content: The curriculum is as decided by the Dental Council of India (DCI). It includes all necessary topics required for application in any dental clinic. Although the syllabus may appear to be very vast, it is doable, especially if you study consistently. There are 3 subjects each in the first, second, and third year, and eight subjects in the final year.

reviews.title: Hitkarni Dental College and Hospital, Jabalpur
reviews.name: Anonymous

content.title: Admission
content.content:
Admission into the college was through the NEET examination; however, one can also take admission through DMAT. We are required to submit the original documents: 12th mark sheet, 10th mark sheet, TC, Passport-size photograph, and Photocopy of Aadhar card. etc.

Eligibility: Any student who has passed 10+2 with PCB is eligible for NEET and henceforth for the college. The application form, date, and fees for the NEET examination are available online. Registration usually starts between April-May.

The admission process is lengthy. Many documents are required.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content:
The course and teachers are friendly and helpful. They will guide you through the 5-year lengthy process of dentistry. The faculty: student ratio varies every year as the subject increases. The students have different subjects each year. There are some subjects like prosthodontics and endodontics which start from the first and second year onwards.
The teachers prefer PowerPoint presentations for teaching and there are practical's to make the students aware of the dynamics of dentistry. The faculty have usually done masters and Ph.D.
There was internals conducted to prepare the students for the finals. That was pretty timely, it was easy to pass the exams owing to friendly teachers.

reviews.title: HCET Jabalpur - a good option for engineers
reviews.name: AJEET TIWARI

content.title: Admission
content.content: Eligibility of the course was higher secondary with a minimum of 50%. The application form was available in the MP Online portal under the head of the admission in technical institutions and after filling out the form the entire counseling was the college's responsibility. I am from the UR category but I got admission under the tuition fee waiver (TFW) Scheme. I would suggest that admission should be purely on merit and not on the reservation.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content: The course curriculum is designed by RAJIV GANDHI PROUDYOGIKI UNIVERSITY (RGPV) and is comprehensive that aims to make student industry ready. The faculty-student ratio was about 1:45. faculty were enough qualified and most of the professors were pursuing Ph.D. in their specialization. Term exams were quarterly and they were of moderate level so you can pass it easily if you are attentive in class.

content.title: Admission
content.content: The admission process is very simple. No, you don't take any entrance exams for college. Admission is based on your jee mains percentile & your 12th percentage. In hitkarni College of engineering, there is no online admission process.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content: I am choosing the CSE branch because in the future there is more scope in this branch and in this college only 60 sheets for the CSE branch So It is very beneficial for students to grab the highest package. teaching methods are very advanced. And having a good Teaching staff.

content.title: Admission
content.content: I applied for three collges for this MDS course first one is Aurobindo dental college indore (MP) second one is Rishiraj dental college and the third one is Hitkarinj dental college jabalpur (MP), so basically at that time i have to choose the collges and accordingly department too , so at the time of choosing I chosen these three colleges and i got allotment of Hitkarini dental college , For admission in MDS course student should have clear his or her NEET MDS exam with qualified marks so after that only they can proceed with other step , well i got 310 marks in NEET MDS exam.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content: I choose this course because I had done my BDS from rungta college Bhilai and I wanted to study so I chose this course, faculty are really nice and there is 2 faculty member in between 9 students because all 9 are PG's, so this course is of 3 years and there are only 2 exams are held first is one 1st year and second is 2nd year.

reviews.name: Poonam ahirwar

content.title: Admission
content.content: College architecture is quite pleasant. Since then, HCET has the biggest infrastructure compared to the other privately held Engineering institutes of Jabalpur. The college has a Central Library has more than 20,000 books. HCET is located in "Dumna" close to IIITDM Jabalpur.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content:
I always have an interest in the IT field because of the same reason I choose this field.
In one department there is an average of 7-8 faculties available. Most of the faculties are PHD holders with great knowledge and experience.
There is a semester exam twice a year and a monthly midterm examination to see the growth of the students.

reviews.review_images_title: Hitkarini College of Engineering and Technology - [HCET]|Jabalpur

reviews.title: A college for self study and aim big
reviews.name: Abhishek Badoniya

content.title: Admission
content.content:
As in my case, I am searching for a college which is in a calm place to study so I choose HCET over others as their campus is far from the city rush and calm area.
The good thing about my college is that teachers are so helpful and the campus has all useful facilities like canteens, hostels, buses, etc.
The admission process is simple to go through JEE mains exam and after that filling counselling or just visit the college and talk to teachers in counselling cell they will guide well. 
The only bad aspect of this college is that due to its located far from the city it's not easy to get the stationery product or other product of study nearby.
I prefer this college if self-study is in your mind as its located in the best location to study as no distraction here.
I didn't go through any blog as I belong to Jabalpur only my elders are also studying in this college they given me more than enough info.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content:
I choose according to my interest in the subject you can choose as per interest.
The faculty is good, not excellent as it's a private college so no one expects excellent but it's good enough and helpful too.
Faculty students ratio is also good.
Faculty is well experienced and top qualified some from NIT and some from big colleges like IIITDM
and their teaching aspect is also good works on every single point of students. 
Term exam held time to time like after half steamer 1 exam and after semester over 1more exam per subject. 
The difficulty level is average if students study well.

content.title: Course Curriculum Overview
content.content: The teachers are very knowledgeable. They provide guidance to students in their exam time. The most teachers are post graduate. The teaching quality is also very good. The teachers takes lesson with practical demonstration. The course curriculum that we are studying is relevant and it makes students ready for industries.

content.title: Placement Experience
content.content: The record of college in providing placements to students is very good. Various companies like Zaro, Infosys visit college campus to provide jobs to students. About 85% students are placed from my branch every year in various marketing and core companies. These companies provide annual package of 3 LPA to 6 LPA.

article.description:
Hitkarni College of Engineering & Technology is known to be a premier technical institute in central India. The College is equipped with first-class amenities and effective training programs for its students. Students seek admission in this institute because of its placement opportunities and quality education.

Hitkarni College intends to produce immaculate technical professionals who can become the future leaders of society. The institute showcases outstanding results of its students and appreciates their efforts by rewarding them. It flaunts of its outstanding infrastructure and eminent faculties.

Hitkarni College of Engineering & Technology Facts and Figures

Year of Foundation

1997

Founder

Hitkarni Sabha

Affiliations

Rajiv Gandhi Proudyogiki Vishwavidyalaya, Bhopal

Institutional area

Spread over 20.72 acres of land with built-up area of 20,954 sq.mts

Admission Through

B.E:-

Based on combined merit scores of JEE exams and XII result

Library

Completely digitised library furnished with:

Total Books: 25720

Journals(national/foreign): 29

E-resources: 1183 (AICTE, INDES etc.)

Laboratory

-6 modular IT centres with 6 networking servers & 250 Pentium IV Computers having latest software applications

Number of Companies visited during last 3 years

Over 35 coveted companies ( 4 companies have already recruited more than 100 students during current year)

% of students placed during last year

85-90%

Waiver scheme

5% for handicapped & Economically backward students

Students extra-curricular activities

Social Welfare club, robotics club, cultural activities etc.

How to reach
  • 17 minutes from Jabalpur Airport, Madhya Pradesh
  • 15 minutes from Jabalpur Railway station
  • 17 minutes from Jabalpur Bus Stand, Jabalpur for inter-city bus services.

Why to Join Hitkarni College of Engineering & Technology?

1. Pioneer Institute under the leadership of award-winning principal: The College is a premier institute in whole of central India and has reached greater heights by the endeavors of its dedicated principal. Mr.S.B.L.Beohar has been honored by the esteemed Rashtriya Shiksha Ratna Award for their researched work in education.

2. Renowned EDUSAT Study centre: The Institute has been selected by RGPV and ISRO as a centre for EDUSAT Project on E-Education programs. Guest faculties and trained teachers give lectures via E-classrooms on selective and innovative topics on different fields.

postAuthor.authorDescription:
Collegedunia is a leading online education platform founded in 2014 by Sahil Chalana, a BITS Pilani alumnus. Over the past 10 years, Collegedunia has established itself as a trusted source of comprehensive and informative data on higher education across dozens of countries.

As an extensive search engine for students, parents, and other stakeholders in the education industry, Collegedunia provides users with the most up-to-date information on colleges, courses, exams, and more.
